# Part 2

## Describe a time when you felt proud of a family member.

One time I felt extremely proud of a family member was last year, when my mother successfully started her own small business after being unemployed for quite a long time.

At that time, the economy wasn’t very good, and many people around her thought she should simply find a stable job instead of taking risks. However, my mother has always been a hardworking and independent person. She decided to open a small online shop selling homemade food and local snacks. At first, things were really difficult. She had to learn how to promote products online, communicate with customers, and manage deliveries all by herself.

I still remember that she often stayed up late watching tutorial videos and learning how online platforms worked. Even though she wasn’t very familiar with technology, she never gave up. Gradually, her business started improving, and she even gained many regular customers because people genuinely liked her products.

I felt especially proud of her because she showed a huge amount of determination and courage. To be honest, many people become afraid of change after reaching middle age, but my mother was willing to step outside her comfort zone and try something completely new.

What impressed me most was not the money she earned, but her attitude. She taught me that failure isn’t something to fear, and that people should continue learning no matter how old they are. As a university student who often feels stressed about the future, I found her experience really inspiring.

Overall, that experience made me admire her even more, and it also motivated me to work harder toward my own goals.

---

### 中文翻译：

有一次我特别为我的家人感到骄傲，那是在去年，我妈妈在失业了很长一段时间后，成功开始了自己的小生意。

当时经济环境并不是很好，很多人都觉得她应该找一份稳定工作，而不是去冒险创业。不过，我妈妈一直都是一个非常努力且独立的人。她决定开一家卖自制食品和地方小吃的网店。

刚开始其实非常困难。她需要自己学习如何在网上推广产品、和顾客沟通，以及处理物流配送。我记得她经常熬夜看教学视频，学习各种电商平台的使用方法。虽然她对科技并不熟悉，但她从来没有放弃。

后来，她的生意慢慢好了起来，甚至拥有了很多固定顾客，因为大家真的很喜欢她做的食物。

我之所以特别为她骄傲，是因为她展现出了巨大的毅力和勇气。说实话，很多人到了中年以后都会害怕改变，但她却愿意走出舒适圈，尝试全新的事情。

最让我佩服的，其实不是她赚了多少钱，而是她的态度。她让我明白，失败并不可怕，而且无论年龄多大，人都应该持续学习。作为一名经常为未来焦虑的大学生，我觉得她的经历特别鼓舞人心。

总的来说，这件事让我更加敬佩她，也激励我更加努力地追求自己的目标。

